translated: Builders, San Francisco, 23-25, engineering high state worker, unemployed, commune member 26, Södertälje city building chief 27-31, head of construction office for Stockholm city's rebuilding work at Slussen 31-35, acting building chief for work at Slussen 36, special assignments for Stockholm city's real estate 37, chief engineer for state harbor and fairway construction in western district since 38. Member of the board for East Södermanland Cultural History Museum in Södertälje 29-31, national antiquarian deputy for Södertälje with mention 29-31. Writings: Work methods for concrete casting for an American dam construction (23), Traffic regulation for Slussen in Stockholm (34), Slussen, the New Traffic Center of Stockholm (35), Foundation of Slussen in Stockholm with Franki piling system (36), Industry and handicrafts in Stockholm, their localization and the general economic conditions for their development (partly 38), Industry and handicrafts in Stockholm (38). RVO. Bjurby, Axel Hilde, clergyman, Målsryd, born on 17/11/00 in Torsby, Värmland. Completed undergraduate studies in Lund in 20, obtained a degree in theology and philosophy in 23, theology candidate, and ordained as a priest in Skara diocese in 28. Assisted pastor in Fägre, became a clergyman in Toarp in 33. Member of church council and child welfare. Note that '\d\d m. partners name' means that the person married in the year 19xx.
